    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged; the assessment team determined that the single-condition F1717 protocol is standard practice for this device class and that the remaining factors collectively provide sufficient credibility for a Medium model risk, Medium decision consequence COU. Validation results across all three QoIs satisfy pre-specified acceptance bounds. The claim that the FEA ensemble accurately predicts compression-bending performance is supported by the validation results documented in this package. Decision: Accepted with the noted test-conditions limitation recorded.",
